comments: Fox (SAC) is moving alongside Siakam's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Fox (SAC) maintains legal guarding position as he contests Siakam's (TOR) driving shot attempt with both arms in a vertical position as he is retreating backwards.

Following the release of his driving shot attempt, Siakiam's (TOR) arm comes down and makes incidental contact with Fox's (SAC) head/face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Barnes (TOR) legally contests Fox's (SAC) driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
Sabonis (SAC) is moving alongside VanVleet's (TOR) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Sabonis (SAC) contests the driving shot attempt and incidental "high-five" contact occurs with VanVleet (TOR) after the release.
Siakam (TOR) does not establish a legal position in Barnes' (SAC) path, when the body contact occurs during Barnes' gather.
Sabonis (SAC) initiates contact with Barnes' (TOR) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Young (TOR) initiates contact with Monk's (SAC) arm during the drive and affects Monk's (SAC) SQBR.
Sabonis (SAC) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during VanVleet's (TOR) driving shot attempt.
VanVleet (TOR) initiates contact with Fox's (SAC) arm as he gains possession of the inbound pass.
Barnes (TOR) inbounds the ball within five seconds.
VanVleet (TOR) delivers contact to Fox (SAC) that dislodges Fox (SAC) from his legally obtained defensive position during the inbound.
